Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
savePtnPin(25.10)                                            savePtnPin(25.10)

Name
       savePtnPin  - Saves the pin assignment information for one or more par-
       titions

Syntax
       savePtnPin

       [-help]

       {-ptn <partitionName> | -all | -design | -selected}

       <fileName>

       Saves the pin assignment information for one or  more  partitions.  You
       can  subsequently  load  the  saved pin assignment information with the
       loadPtnPin command. The savePtnPin command also saves the  pin  assign-
       ment information for blackboxes.

Parameters
       -all   Specifies  that pin assignment information will be saved for all
              partitions, including the top-level design.

              Default: By default, the savePtnPin command saves  the  pin  as-
              signment information for all partitions.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -design
              Specifies that pin assignment information will be saved only for
              the top-level design.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       <fileName>
              Specifies  the  name  of the file in which the partition pin as-
              signment information will be saved.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each  savePtnPin parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command: man savePtnPin

       -ptn <partitionName>
              Specifies the name of the partition for which the pin assignment
              information is to be saved.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -selected
              Specifies  that the pin assignment information will be saved for
              all the selected pins of the partitions, including the top-level
              design.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The following command saves the pin assignment information for the par-
       tition named tdsp_block into a file named tdsp_block_pin_info.

       savePtnPin -ptn tdsp_block tdsp_block_pin_info

